✅ Étape 1 — stocker metrics dans Run
Ajoute dans Run :
Java
private long sparkInputRecords;
private long sparkOutputRecords;
private long sparkInputBytes;
private long sparkOutputBytes;

public void setSparkMetrics(long inRec, long outRec, long inBytes, long outBytes) {
    this.sparkInputRecords = inRec;
    this.sparkOutputRecords = outRec;
    this.sparkInputBytes = inBytes;
    this.sparkOutputBytes = outBytes;
}
✅ Étape 2 — SparkListener
Java
public class SparkMetricsListener extends SparkListener {

    private final Run run;

    private long inRec = 0;
    private long outRec = 0;
    private long inBytes = 0;
    private long outBytes = 0;

    public SparkMetricsListener(Run run) {
        this.run = run;
    }

    @Override
    public void onTaskEnd(SparkListenerTaskEnd taskEnd) {

        TaskMetrics m = taskEnd.taskMetrics();
        if (m == null) return;

        if (m.inputMetrics() != null) {
            inBytes += m.inputMetrics().bytesRead();
            inRec += m.inputMetrics().recordsRead();
        }

        if (m.outputMetrics() != null) {
            outBytes += m.outputMetrics().bytesWritten();
            outRec += m.outputMetrics().recordsWritten();
        }
    }

    @Override
    public void onJobEnd(SparkListenerJobEnd jobEnd) {

        run.setSparkMetrics(inRec, outRec, inBytes, outBytes);
    }
}
✅ Étape 3 — enregistrer AVANT runPipeline
Dans ton PipelineRunner :
Java
spark.sparkContext().addSparkListener(
    new SparkMetricsListener(run)
);
✅ Étape 4 — utiliser dans ton MonitoringService
Dans ton insert SQL ajoute :
SQL
spark_input_records
spark_output_records
spark_input_bytes
spark_output_bytes
Et dans Java :
Java
ps.setLong(XX, run.getSparkInputRecords());
ps.setLong(XX, run.getSparkOutputRecords());
ps.setLong(XX, run.getSparkInputBytes());
ps.setLong(XX, run.getSparkOutputBytes());
⚠️ Important
👉 Les metrics seront dispo UNIQUEMENT à la fin du job
Donc :
OK dans RunInSuccessEvent
OK dans RunInErrorEvent
❌ PAS dans RunInStartEvent
